---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Quvii"
  description="Quvii is a connected-security technology brand researching the cameras, sensors, and software shaping how the modern home protects itself."
>
  <div class="container-page py-14 lg:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <p class="text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-primary-600">About</p>
      <h1 class="mt-4 font-display text-display-sm sm:text-display tracking-display text-ink leading-[1.05]">
        Connected security, refined.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-body-muted leading-relaxed">
        Quvii is a US-headquartered technology brand focused on connected
        security for the modern home. We research the cameras, sensors, and
        software that decide what a home sees, what it remembers, and who gets
        to ask.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-14 lg:mt-20 grid gap-14 lg:grid-cols-3">
      <div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink">What we work on</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-body leading-relaxed">
          Wireless and PoE cameras, video doorbells, floodlight systems,
          indoor monitors, and the network + software stack that ties them
          together — across Ring, Eufy, Reolink, Blink, Arlo, Nest, Wyze,
          Lorex, Amcrest, Hikvision, Dahua, and Imou.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink">How we operate</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-body leading-relaxed">
          Independent of every device manufacturer. No paid placements, no
          embargoed launch participation, no review-copy strings. Conclusions
          are grounded in measurement, manufacturer documentation, and
          long-running community evidence — not marketing claims.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink">What's ahead</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-body leading-relaxed">
          Quvii's roadmap is product-forward: an in-house line of connected
          security hardware engineered around the principles laid out across
          this site. Today, we publish the research. Tomorrow, we ship the
          systems built on it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <hr class="my-16 border-body-line" />

    <div class="grid gap-12 lg:grid-cols-2">
      <div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink">Who runs Quvii</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-body leading-relaxed">
          Quvii is owned and operated by Quvii Inc., a US-headquartered
          technology company. Office address will be published as part of
          our brand launch.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 text-body leading-relaxed">
          For research, partnership, or press: <strong>hello@quvii.com</strong>.
          For factual corrections to anything published on this site:
          <strong>corrections@quvii.com</strong>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink">How we sustain the work</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-body leading-relaxed">
          Two disclosed channels. We participate in
          <a href="/affiliate-disclosure/" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 underline decoration-primary-300">Amazon Associates</a>
          on a flat per-category basis, which removes the financial incentive to
          rank one product over another. We run a small volume of automated
          Google AdSense placements on long-form content. Direct ad inventory
          is not for sale.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 text-body leading-relaxed">
          The standards we hold work to are published in detail —
          <a href="/editorial-policy/" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 underline decoration-primary-300">read them here</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
